author: maxb
msg: SWIG: Consolidate OUTPUT_OF_CONST_CHAR_P and OUTPUT_OF_PROP typemaps,
providing wrappings for svn_wc_get_default_ignores() and svn_wc_get_ignores()
for Perl, as a side-effect.
[in subversion/bindings/swig/]
* include/svn_containers.swg: Consolidate typemaps and applications.
* svn_fs.i, svn_repos.i: Delete applications no longer required.

author: maxb
msg: SWIG: Consolidate Ruby '(in) apr_hash_t *hash' typemap with the PROPHASH
typemap, incidentally improving the wrapping of svn_config_write_auth_data()
for Python.
* subversion/bindings/swig/include/svn_containers.swg

author: maxb
msg: SWIG: Tidy up apr_hash_t * <const char *, const char *> input.
* svn_fs.i, svn_ra.i, svn_repos.i: Remove STRING_TO_STRING application.
* include/svn_containers.swg: Consolidate STRING_TO_STRING and Ruby fs_config
typemaps under new names HASH_CSTRING and HASH_CSTRING_MAYBENULL,
leaving FIXMEs for Python and Perl which lack handling of the MAYBENULL
case. Do the application of these typemaps centrally at the point of
definition, too.
